divine mind within the world as sensible light, which reveals the world
to the the senses and sustains it. The perfect reflexivity (^splendore~)
of consciousness corresponds to light (being, truth, the power to see);
its re-reflection corresponds to contingent attributes and identity,
what is seen. The first reflection is invariable and self-subsistent;
the re-reflection is variable and contingent" (C. Moevs, ^The Metaphysics
